subSubSection.paragraph:
Radula
. Formula 15×1.1(0).1; lateral teeth curved (
Figs. 5A, B
), tapering at the top and bottom, with denticulation in the middle of the inner edge (
Figs. 5C
, 
6A
); they can diverge far from each other (
Fig. 4C
) providing wide grip. Tips of lateral teeth covered with chitin crown ca. 
100 µm
in length (
Fig. 5B
). Rachidian teeth rectangular (fig. 6A); vestigial, located in immature part of radular tape (
Fig. 4F
), and in some posterior working rows of radula.

Digestive tract
. Small buccal mass connects dorsally to short wide esophagus and short narrow twisted salivary glands (
Fig. 4D
). Two strong muscle retractors attach to posterior end of buccal mass. Esophagus with thin-walled expansion (crop), opening into large muscular gizzard (
Fig. 4B
). Gizzard with tree gizzard plates. Paired plates large, irregularly-oval (sub-quadrate) (
Figs. 4B, E
, 
5E, F
). Unpaired plate narrow, flattened laterally (
Figs. 4G
, 
5G
). All three plates with central thick area and thinner periphery. Microsculpture of periphery consists of small pits and tubercles (
Fig. 5F
3
); narrow area between central part and periphery consists of irregularly arranged polygons (
Fig. 5F
1
); polygons of central area filled with reticular matrix (
Figs. 5F
2
).

Male copulatory system . Prostate cylindrical ( Fig. 4H ), rounded at the end. Prostate connected with penial sac by narrow duct folded near the sac. Penial sac (
Fig. 4I
) elongate, divided into anterior part with fold-like penis and posterior part with curved strand of vacuolated cells (probably for supporting functions).

